-- Lukoil’s CEO Vagit Alekperov Buys $5.3 Million in Company Stock
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-01-20T10:07:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/lukoil-s-ceo-vagit-alekperov-buys-5-3-million-in-company-stock.html
OAO Lukoil’s (LKOH)  Chief Executive Officer
 Vagit Alekperov  bought 165.5 million rubles ($5.3 million) worth
of shares in the company this week.  Alekperov bought 57,000 shares on Jan. 18 and an additional
35,000 shares yesterday, Russia’s second-largest oil producer
said today in a statement. The company’s market capitalization
is about $49 billion, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
